				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1095276">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Hey fellow sorcerers,<br />
<br />
I have experimented that thing as well. Usually I get the &quot;Invis will fade&quot; message in the minute (2 or 3 when I'm lucky, but maybe that's it, me being just unlucky) of casting invis.<br />
A few solutions would be (not limitative here):<br />
<br />
1) Bring it back to what it was, although this is felt as being overpowered by the developpers, enabling full groups to get to the bosses of dungeons too easily,<br />
<br />
2) Bring it back to what it was but make it self so that we can get a full group sneaking through a whole dungeon right to the boss. Main problem here is that it removes one of our only utility in group beside DPS (thought I think we have a single target mezz later, I'm only level 12),<br />
<br />
3) Renew properly invis when it's recast as, as already stated, the new one will fade as if the spell hadn't been refreshed once you've had the message. Only problem here is that we would be exactly in the same position as in 1) with just a few casts more,<br />
<br />
4) Make invis drop when you cast another invis (would force us to make sure we refresh it in a proper place),<br />
<br />
5) Give it a proper minimum duration. 1 min sounds a bit low.<br />
<br />
I'm sure plenty of other solutions exist. I'd personnaly would like to see the refresh bug corrected.<br />
<br />
Moonskin Starfire<br />
Gelenia<br />
<br />
PS: sorry for my poor english but if it's too much trouble, next time I'll post in french :P
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
